title: Radiative capture cross sections of tellurium isotopes as a function of neutron energies up to 1.5 keV

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Soviet Atomic Energy, Vol.14, p.258 (1964)

x4freetext: Radiative capture cross sections of tellurium isotopes
as a function of neutron energies up to 1.5 keV
.Neutrons produced from a uranium target of the linear
accelerator surrounded by a 4 cm water moderator.
Neutron pulse length was either 0.9 or 0.6 microsec.
Distance from neutron source to sample - 15.1 m.
Neutron flux form for energies up to 400 eV on the
Time of flight. Time channel width 0.05 microsec,
half width of the resolution function 0.05 microsec/m.
At cross-section measurement a Cd filter of 0.5 mm
thickness was placed in the path of the beam.
of 70-80 mm diameter, 55-60 mm high, for gamma
.Corrections were made for Doppler broadening, multiple
independent of time-of-flight - 3% of counts with a
depending on time-of-flight - 75% of total background
